@{
    Layout = "~/_Layout.cshtml";
}

@section banner{
    <h1>Exploring BootStrap to Format Page</h1>
}

<blockquote class="alert alert-info">
    Bootstrap is a css style sheet create as open source. It contains about 10,000 lines of css code. Using various aspects of this style
    sheet can allow us to quick via classes block format our web page. It will also allow for text alignment, setting up nicely formated
    grid displays, create color buttons, banners, etc. Alert allows for color blocking an area plus other stuff. 4 basic alert colors can
    be obtained by using alert-success, alert-info, alert-warning and alert-danger.
    Default block alignment is left. You can change that using text-xxxxx where xxxxx is left, right, and center.
    <br/>
    WARNING: Bootstrap is open-source third-party and is subject to change. Thus items that were once available may NOT be available
    in the future.
</blockquote>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        left block
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3 text-center">
        center block
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5 text-right">
        right block
    </div>
</div>
<hr style="height:5px;"/>
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="alert alert-success">
            left text content
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3 text-capitalize text-center text-dark">
        <div class="alert alert-warning">
            center text content
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5">
        <div class="alert alert-danger">
            right text content
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
